Package it.polimi.ingsw.Server

Class Session

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.Observer.Observable<Message>
it.polimi.ingsw.Server.Session
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Session
extends Observable<Message>
implements java.io.Serializable
A Session is used to handle the pre-match. A "challenger" creates a Session where other Client may join via PlayerSelectSession message.

    • addParticipant

      public void addParticipant​(ClientConnection player)
      When a Client succesful join a Session it will be added in the waitingConnection map which will be cleared after its size reach the number of players selected for the Game in the constructor. When this occurs a start method will be used to create the real Game on the server and the match will start.
